.TH "bond_opt_get" 9 "bond_opt_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bond_opt_get \- get a pointer to an option
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct bond_option *" bond_opt_get
.BI "(unsigned int option "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "option" 12
option for which to return a pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks if option is valid and if so returns a pointer
to its entry in the bond_opts[] option array.
